<% content_for :title, "Managing Bookings — Admin Manual" %>

<div class="flex gap-8 lg:gap-12">
  <aside class="hidden lg:block w-52 flex-shrink-0">
    <%= render "sidebar" %>
  </aside>

  <article class="min-w-0 flex-1">
    <%= render BreadcrumbComponent.new(items: [
      { label: "Admin Manual", path: admin_docs_path },
      { label: "Bookings", path: nil }
    ]) %>

    <h1 class="mt-3 text-2xl font-semibold text-stone-900">Managing Bookings</h1>
    <p class="mt-2 text-stone-500">View, filter, create, and cancel bookings from the Bookings section.</p>

    <div class="mt-8 space-y-8 text-stone-700">
      <section>
        <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-stone-900">Booking Statuses</h2>
        <div class="mt-3 text-sm">
          <table class="w-full rounded-xl border border-stone-200 overflow-hidden text-left">
            <thead class="bg-stone-50 text-xs uppercase tracking-wide text-stone-500">
              <tr>
                <th class="px-4 py-2 font-semibold">Status</th>
                <th class="px-4 py-2 font-semibold">What it means</th>
              </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody class="divide-y divide-stone-100 bg-white">
              <tr>
                <td class="px-4 py-3 font-medium">Pending</td>
                <td class="px-4 py-3 text-stone-600">Customer is in checkout; payment not yet confirmed</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td class="px-4 py-3 font-medium">Confirmed</td>
                <td class="px-4 py-3 text-stone-600">Payment successful; session is locked in</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td class="px-4 py-3 font-medium">Cancelled</td>
                <td class="px-4 py-3 text-stone-600">Cancelled by the customer or by you</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td class="px-4 py-3 font-medium">Completed</td>
                <td class="px-4 py-3 text-stone-600">Session has taken place — set automatically once all slots have ended</td>
              </tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-stone-900">Filtering and Viewing Bookings</h2>
        <div class="mt-3 space-y-3 text-sm">
          <p>
            Go to <strong>Bookings</strong> to see all bookings. Use the filter tabs at the top to
            narrow by status. Click any booking to see full details: customer info, all session times,
            total paid, Stripe payment and receipt links, and refund status if applicable.
          </p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-stone-900">Creating a Manual Booking</h2>
        <div class="mt-3 space-y-3 text-sm">
          <p>
            Go to <strong>Bookings → New Booking</strong>. Useful when a customer calls or emails
            instead of booking online.
          </p>
          <ol class="mt-3 space-y-2 list-decimal pl-5">
            <li>Select the customer from the dropdown (create them first under <strong>Customers</strong> if needed)</li>
            <li>Select the open slots for their session</li>
            <li>Optionally add internal notes</li>
            <li>Optionally generate a <strong>Stripe Payment Link</strong> — a URL you can email so the customer pays online</li>
          </ol>
          <p>
            The booking is created as <strong>Confirmed</strong> immediately. No payment is required
            upfront if you're handling it another way or if it's a comp session.
          </p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-stone-900">Cancelling a Booking</h2>
        <div class="mt-3 space-y-3 text-sm">
          <p>
            From any booking detail page, click <strong>Cancel Booking</strong>. If the booking was
            paid via Stripe, the app automatically issues a full refund to the customer's card. The
            slots are released back to open and the customer receives a push notification.
          </p>
          <p>
            Admin cancellations always refund the customer in full, regardless of the cancellation
            window set in Settings.
          </p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-stone-900">Bulk Cancellation</h2>
        <div class="mt-3 text-sm">
          <p>
            From the Bookings list, select multiple bookings using their checkboxes and use the
            <strong>Cancel Selected</strong> action to cancel them all at once.
          </p>
        </div>
      </section>
    </div>
  </article>
</div>
